    <statement><p>The winner of a <m>4\ {\rm mi}</m> race finishes <m>7.49\ {\rm min}</m> ahead of the second-place runner.  On average, the winner ran <m>0.7\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut mi}{\rm\mathstrut hr}}</m> faster than the second place runner.  Find the average running speed for each runner.</p>
<p>The winner's average speed was <fillin characters="15" name="AnSwEr0001"/> and the second-place runner's average speed was <fillin characters="15" name="AnSwEr0002"/>.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5.1\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut mi}{\rm\mathstrut hr}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>4.4\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut mi}{\rm\mathstrut hr}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
